tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T21 at Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December...Played in nine events on PGA TOUR Canada and recorded two top-10 finishes. After missing the cut at PC Financial Open, went on to card rounds of 68-67-71-67 at Bayview Place Island Savings Open for a T17 finish...First top-10 finish of the season came at the Staal Foundation Open. He was third, with rounds of 66-72-67-69 to finish three strokes behind champion Wes Homan's 271 total...Two starts later, earned second top-10 with a T7 at the Wildfire Invitational to move into the top 25 in the season-long Order of Merit. 

2011: Made the cut at the Nationwide Children's Hospital Classic...Earned Hooters Tour Player of the Year honors. Has made the cut in all three prior Web.com Tour starts. 2007: Turned in his best Web.com Tour finish, a T10 at the Miccosukee Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Finished second at the 1997 State Championships while at Lake Brantley High School in Altamonte Springs, Fla.
tourBios.personal: Worked as a golf shop assistant since college...Is a self-taught player...Favorite courses he has played are Bay Hill Club and Lodge in Orlando and TPC Sawgrass...Never travels without an Xbox...Uses a 1965 quarter to mark his ball...Favorite food is fajitas. Favorite vacation spot is the Florida Keys...Carries Uncrustables in his golf bag for a snack...Dream foursome would include Arnold Palmer, Jack Nicklaus and Tiger Woods...Not many know he owns a Harley-Davidson motorcycle.
